byerleyana
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
(A) Dorsal view, 
<emphasis box="[683,751,1623,1644]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">in vivo</emphasis>
. (B) Ventral view of the live specimen showing the pharynx, uteri, and sucker. (C) Close-up of the anterior region showing the pseudoentacles and the cerebral, pre-cerebral, and marginal eyes; ce: cerebral eyes; me: marginal eyes; mt: marginal tentacles; pe: pre-cerebral eyes; ph: pharynx; su: sucker; u: uteri.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1750,2027]" lastBlockId="15.[151,1437,151,608]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="252" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,423,1750,1775]" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">External anatomy.</emphasis>
Large, oval, and elongated body with ruffled margins. Dorsal surface light brown with well-defined roundish cream circles of different sizes forming a reticulate pattern. Presence of smaller circles between the interstices of the larger. Midline with a darker brown coloration and larger and more spaced rings becoming smaller and more numerous toward the margin (
<figureCitation box="[848,943,1858,1883]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,456,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,445,1577]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pericelis byerleyana. (A) Dorsal view, in vivo. (B) Ventral view of the live specimen showing the pharynx, uteri, and sucker. (C) Close-up of the anterior region showing the pseudoentacles and the cerebral, pre-cerebral, and marginal eyes; ce: cerebral eyes; me: marginal eyes; mt: marginal tentacles; pe: pre-cerebral eyes; ph: pharynx; su: sucker; u: uteri." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Light brown ventral surface lacking the reticulate pattern (
<figureCitation box="[361,451,1894,1919]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,456,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,445,1577]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pericelis byerleyana. (A) Dorsal view, in vivo. (B) Ventral view of the live specimen showing the pharynx, uteri, and sucker. (C) Close-up of the anterior region showing the pseudoentacles and the cerebral, pre-cerebral, and marginal eyes; ce: cerebral eyes; me: marginal eyes; mt: marginal tentacles; pe: pre-cerebral eyes; ph: pharynx; su: sucker; u: uteri." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Indistinct, small pseudotentacles formed by simple folds of the anterior margin and with numerous pseudotentacular eyes at the tip (
<figureCitation box="[702,792,1930,1955]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,456,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,445,1577]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pericelis byerleyana. (A) Dorsal view, in vivo. (B) Ventral view of the live specimen showing the pharynx, uteri, and sucker. (C) Close-up of the anterior region showing the pseudoentacles and the cerebral, pre-cerebral, and marginal eyes; ce: cerebral eyes; me: marginal eyes; mt: marginal tentacles; pe: pre-cerebral eyes; ph: pharynx; su: sucker; u: uteri." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). Cerebral eyes arranged in two elongated and separated clusters located in a clear area. More numerous eyes posteriorly extending to thin lines of less and more scattered eyes anteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[330,429,2002,2027]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,456,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,445,1577]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pericelis byerleyana. (A) Dorsal view, in vivo. (B) Ventral view of the live specimen showing the pharynx, uteri, and sucker. (C) Close-up of the anterior region showing the pseudoentacles and the cerebral, pre-cerebral, and marginal eyes; ce: cerebral eyes; me: marginal eyes; mt: marginal tentacles; pe: pre-cerebral eyes; ph: pharynx; su: sucker; u: uteri." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294702/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="251">Figs. 8C</figureCitation>
). Marginal eyes surrounding the entire body. In the anterior area, few pre-cerebral eyes are also present (
<figureCitation box="[305,396,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,456,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,445,1577]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pericelis byerleyana. (A) Dorsal view, in vivo. (B) Ventral view of the live specimen showing the pharynx, uteri, and sucker. (C) Close-up of the anterior region showing the pseudoentacles and the cerebral, pre-cerebral, and marginal eyes; ce: cerebral eyes; me: marginal eyes; mt: marginal tentacles; pe: pre-cerebral eyes; ph: pharynx; su: sucker; u: uteri." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294702/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
). A large ruffled pharynx, highly branched located centrally (
<figureCitation box="[1111,1201,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,456,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,445,1577]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pericelis byerleyana. (A) Dorsal view, in vivo. (B) Ventral view of the live specimen showing the pharynx, uteri, and sucker. (C) Close-up of the anterior region showing the pseudoentacles and the cerebral, pre-cerebral, and marginal eyes; ce: cerebral eyes; me: marginal eyes; mt: marginal tentacles; pe: pre-cerebral eyes; ph: pharynx; su: sucker; u: uteri." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294702/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
). Separate male and female gonopores. The male gonopore is located immediately after the pharynx and the female pore close to male gonopore. Small sucker located posteriorly and close to the female gonopore (
<figureCitation box="[1025,1113,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,456,1566]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,445,1577]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Pericelis byerleyana. (A) Dorsal view, in vivo. (B) Ventral view of the live specimen showing the pharynx, uteri, and sucker. (C) Close-up of the anterior region showing the pseudoentacles and the cerebral, pre-cerebral, and marginal eyes; ce: cerebral eyes; me: marginal eyes; mt: marginal tentacles; pe: pre-cerebral eyes; ph: pharynx; su: sucker; u: uteri." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1294702/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">Fig. 8B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
