<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="252" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,260,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">Taxonomic remarks.</emphasis>
Currently, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Laidlaw" authorityYear="1902" box="[704,804,260,285]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[704,804,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">Pericelis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contains four valid species (
<bibRefCitation box="[1143,1291,260,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" refId="ref12761" refString="Faubel, A. (1984) The Polycladida, Turbellaria Proposal and establishment of a new system Part II. The Cotylea. Mitteilungen Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 81, 189 ¯ 259." type="journal article">Faubel 1984</bibRefCitation>
; Tyler 
<emphasis box="[1376,1429,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">et al</emphasis>
. 
<date box="[151,281,295,320]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" value="2006" valueMax="2018">2006–2018</date>
), mainly distinguished by the color and pattern. Of these, 
<emphasis box="[957,1214,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collingwood" authorityYear="1876" box="[957,1115,295,320]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="byerleyana">P. byerleyana</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1129,1210,297,320]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="cata">P. cata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1274,1436,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmarda" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1274,1431,295,320]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="orbicularis">P. orbicularis</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
share a similar reticulated brown pattern. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[782,861,333,356]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="cata">
<emphasis box="[782,861,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. cata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collingwood" authorityYear="1876" box="[1034,1193,332,357]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="byerleyana">
<emphasis box="[1034,1193,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. byerleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the conspicuous pseudotentacles with black tips, patchy background with irregular-shaped white circles, and a few black spots scattered over the dorsal surface. On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmarda" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[772,924,404,429]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis box="[772,924,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a dark brown pigment forming a loose network pattern instead of well-defined white rings as seen in 
<emphasis box="[859,1019,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collingwood" authorityYear="1876" box="[859,1015,439,464]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="byerleyana">P. byerleyana</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Moreover, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmarda" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[1151,1304,439,464]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis box="[1151,1304,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a more developed sucker. Despite their morphological similarity, a comparison based on available molecular data for 
<taxonomicName class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="cata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. cata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<accessionNumber box="[216,342,511,536]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/EU679114" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">EU679114</accessionNumber>
), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmarda" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[363,517,511,536]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis box="[363,517,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<accessionNumber box="[533,660,511,536]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/EU679116" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">EU679116</accessionNumber>
), and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collingwood" authorityYear="1876" box="[730,884,511,536]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="byerleyana">
<emphasis box="[730,884,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. byerleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<accessionNumber box="[900,1035,512,536]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH047291" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">MH047291</accessionNumber>
), using about 950 base pairs of the 28S rDNA gene, revealed species-specific changes allowing us to clearly distinguish three different species (
<tableCitation captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="15.[151,239,650,673]" captionText="TABLE 3. Distance matrix for members of the genus Pericelis showing percentage of nucleotide similarity among sequences." pageId="15" pageNumber="252">Table 3</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
