<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1039,1245]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">
In addition, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collingwood" authorityYear="1876" box="[336,489,1039,1064]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="byerleyana">
<emphasis box="[336,489,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. byerleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been frequently found in the Indian Ocean and the Indo-Pacific region whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[151,227,1077,1100]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="cata">
<emphasis box="[151,227,1077,1100]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. cata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Schmarda" baseAuthorityYear="1859" box="[284,437,1076,1101]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="orbicularis">
<emphasis box="[284,437,1076,1101]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. orbicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been found in the Atlantic Ocean including the Caribbean and the Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[1350,1436,1076,1101]" name="Mexico" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">
<collectingRegion box="[1350,1436,1076,1101]" country="Mexico" name="Mexico" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">Mexico</collectingRegion>
</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[158,367,1111,1136]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" refId="ref16238" refString="Schmmarda, L. K. (1859) Neue Turbellarien, Rotatorien und Anneliden beobachtet und gesammelt auf einer Reise um die Erde 1853 bis 1857. Neue Wirbellose thiere, I, 1 - 66, 15 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 85313" type="journal article">Schmmarda 1859</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[385,555,1111,1136]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" refId="ref13532" refString="Hyman, L. H. (1955 b) A further study of the polyclad flatworms of the west Indian region. Bulletin of Marine Science of the Gulf and Caribbean, 5, 259 - 268." type="journal article">Hyman 1955b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[573,863,1111,1136]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" refId="ref14439" refString="Marcus, E. &amp; Marcus, E. (1968) Polycladida from Curacao and faunistically related regions. Studies on the Fauna of Curacao and other Caribbean Islands, 101, 1 ¯ 133." type="journal article">Marcus &amp; Marcus 1968</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[881,1124,1111,1136]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" refId="ref15847" refString="Quiroga, S. Y., Bolanos, D. M. &amp; Litvaitis, M. K. (2004) A checklist of polyclad Flatworms (Platyhelminthes: Polycladida) from the Caribbean coast of Colombia, South America. Zootaxa, 633 (1), 1 - 12. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 633.1.1" type="journal article">
Quiroga 
<emphasis box="[987,1042,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">et al</emphasis>
. 2004
</bibRefCitation>
). A previous record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Collingwood" authorityYear="1876" class="Rhabditophora" family="Pericelidae" genus="Pericelis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="byerleyana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">P. byerleyana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was poorly presented by 
<bibRefCitation box="[583,762,1148,1173]" pageId="15" pageNumber="252" refId="ref15733" refString="Prudhoe, S. (1989) Polyclad turbellarians recorded from African Waters. Bulletin of the British Museum of Natural History, 55 (1), 47 - 96." type="journal article">Prudhoe (1989)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<collectingCountry box="[817,883,1148,1173]" name="Israel" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">Israel</collectingCountry>
. Thus, we present a detailed description of the species based on the external morphology, high quality photographs, and molecular sequence data (
<accessionNumber box="[1257,1390,1184,1208]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/MH047291" pageId="15" pageNumber="252">MH047291</accessionNumber>
) for future comparisons with other pericelid species.
</paragraph>
